class KadasAnnotationLayerRegistry : QObject
{
%Docstring(signature="appended")
Process-wide registry of the well-known singleton Kadas \c
:py:class:`QgsAnnotationLayer` instances inside the current \c
:py:class:`QgsProject`.

Each \c StandardLayer enum value names a *role* (Redlining, Symbols,
Pictures, Pins, Routes, MSS) that the application auto-creates the first
time a tool needs a destination layer for that role. There is at most
one layer per role per project; subsequent lookups return the existing
instance. The mapping from role to project layer id is persisted under a
dedicated \c StandardAnnotationLayers element in the project XML.

Configurable / parametric annotation layers (bullseye, guidegrid) are
deliberately out of scope: each instance carries its own configuration
and a project can hold many of them, so they cannot be keyed by a fixed
role. Those are handled by \c KadasAnnotationLayer + its promotion
registry instead.
%End

%TypeHeaderCode
#include "kadas/gui/annotationitems/kadasannotationlayerregistry.h"
%End
  public:
    enum class StandardLayer
    {
      RedliningLayer,
      SymbolsLayer,
      PicturesLayer,
      PinsLayer,
      RoutesLayer,
      MssLayer
    };

    static QgsAnnotationLayer *getOrCreateAnnotationLayer( StandardLayer layer );
%Docstring
adding it to the current project on first use.
%End


    static void init();
%Docstring
Connects to project signals; must be called once at app startup.
%End

  protected:
    KadasAnnotationLayerRegistry();

};

